= 2010.2 =
Notable features van deze versie zijn greatly simplified object navigatie; virtual buffers voor Adobe Flash content; access to many previously inaccessible controls by retrieving text written to de scherm; flat review of scherm text; ondersteuning voor IBM Lotus Symphony documents; reporting of tabel row en kolom hoofdingen in Mozilla Firefox; en significantly improved user documentatie.

== Nieuwe Functies ==
- Navigating through objects met de review cursor has been greatly simplified. de review cursor nu excludes objects which aren't useful to de user; i.e. objects only used voor layout purposes en unavailable objects.
- In applicaties using de Java Access Bridge (including OpenOffice.org), formatting can nu be reported in text controls. (#358, #463)
- Als moving de muis over cells in Microsoft Excel, NVDA will appropriately announce them.
- In applicaties using de Java Access Bridge, de text of een dialog is nu reported als de dialog appears. (#554)
- een virtualBuffer can nu be used to navigate adobe Flash content. Object navigatie en interacting met de controls directly (by turning on focus mode) is still ondersteund. (#453)
- bewerkbare text controls in de Eclipse IDE, including de code editor, are nu accessible. You must be using Eclipse 3.6 or later. (#256, #641)
- NVDA can nu retrieve most text written to de scherm. (#40, #643)
 - This allows voor reading of controls which do not expose informatie in more direct/reliable ways.
 - Controls made accessible by this feature include: some menu items which display icons (b.v. de Open met menu on files in Windows XP) (#151), bewerkbare text velden in Windows Live applicaties (#200), de fouten lijst in Outlook Express (#582), de bewerkbare text control in TextPad (#605), lists in Eudora, many controls in Australian E-tax en de formula bar in Microsoft Excel.
- ondersteuning voor de code editor in Microsoft Visual Studio 2005 en 2008. At least Visual Studio Standard is required; this does not work in de Express editions. (#457)
- ondersteuning voor IBM Lotus Symphony documents.
- Early experimental ondersteuning voor Google Chrome. Please note that Chrome's scherm reader support is far from complete en additional work may also be required in NVDA. You will need een recent development build of Chrome to try this.
- de state of toggle keys (caps lock, num lock en scroll lock) is nu displayed in braille als they are pressed. (#620)
- Help balloons are nu displayed in braille als they appear. (#652)
- Added een driver voor de MDV Lilli brailleleesregel. (#241)
- Als selecting een entire row or kolom in Microsoft Excel met de shortcut keys shift+space en control+space, de nieuw selection is nu reported. (#759)
- tabel row en kolom hoofdingen can nu be reported. This is configurable from de Document Formatting preferences dialog.
 - Currently, this is ondersteund in documents in Mozilla applicaties zoals Firefox (version 3.6.11 en later) en Thunderbird (version 3.1.5 en later). (#361)
- Introduced commands voor flat review: (#58)
 - NVDA+numpad7  switches to flat review, placing de review cursor at de position of de current object, allowing you  to review de scherm (or een document if within one) met de text review commands.
 - NVDA+numpad1 moves de review cursor into de object represented by de text at  de position of de review cursor, allowing you to navigate by object from that point.
- Current NVDA user settings can be  copied to be used on secure Windows schermen zoals de logon en UAC schermen by pressing een button in de General Settings dialog. (#730)
- ondersteuning voor Mozilla Firefox 4.
- ondersteuning voor Microsoft Internet Explorer 9.


== veranderingen ==
- de sayAll by Navigator object (NVDA+numpadAdd), navigator object volgende in flow (NVDA+shift+numpad6) en navigator object vorige in flow (NVDA+shift+numpad4) commands have been removed voor de time being, due to bugginess en to free up de keys voor andere mogelijk features.
- In de NVDA Synthesizer dialog, only de display name of de synthesizer is nu listed. Previously, het was prefixed by de driver's name, which is only relevant internally.
- Als in embedded applicaties or virtual buffers inside een andere virtualBuffer (b.v. Flash), you can nu  press nvda+control+space to move out of de embedded applicatie or virtual buffer to de containing document. Previously nvda+space  was used voor this. nu nvda+space is specifically only voor toggling brows/focus modes on virtualBuffers.
