== Speech ==
- NVDA nu comes packaged met eSpeak 1.33 which contains many improvements, among those are improved talen, named variants, ability to speak faster.
- de voice settings dialog nu allows you to change de variant of een synthesizer if het supports one. Variant is usually een slight variatie on de current voice. (eSpeak supports variants).
- Added de ability to change de inflection of een voice in de voice settings dialog if de current synthesizer supports this. (eSpeak supports inflection).
- Added de ability to turn off speaking of object position informatie(b.v. 1 of 4). This option can be found in de Object presentatie settings dialog.
- NVDA can nu beep als speaking een capital letter. This can be turned on en off met een check box in de voice settings dialog. Also added een raise pitch voor capitals check box to configure whether NVDA should actually do its normal pitch raise voor capitals. So nu you can have either raise pitch, say cap, or beep, voor capitals.
- Added de ability to pause speech in NVDA (like found in Voice Over voor de Mac). Als NVDA is speaking something, you can press de control or shift keys to silence speech just like normal, but if you then tap de shift toets opnieuw (as long as you havn't pressed any andere keys) speech will continue from exactly where het left off.
- Added een virtual synthDriver which outputs text to een venster instead of speaking via een speech synthesiser. This should be more pleasant voor sighted developers who are not used to speech synthesis but want to know what is spoken by NVDA. There are probably still some bugs, so feedback is most definitely welcome.
- NVDA niet langer by standaard speaks punctuatie, you can enable speaking of punctuatie met NVDA+p.
- eSpeak by standaard nu speaks quite een bit slower, which should make het easier voor people who are using eSpeak voor de first time, als installing or starting to use NVDA.
- Added user dictionaries to NVDA. These allow you to make NVDA speak certain text differently. There are three dictionaries: standaard, voice, en temporary. Entries you add to de standaard dictionary will happen all de time in NVDA. Voice dictionaries are specific to de current synthesizer en voice you currently have set. en temporary dictionary is  voor those times you quickly want to set een rule while you are doing een particular task, but you don't want het to be perminant (it will disappear if you close NVDA). voor nu de rules are regular expressions, not just normal text.
- Synthesizers can nu use any audio output device on your system, by setting de output device combo box in de Synthesizer dialog before selecting de synthesizer you want.


