== muis ==
- verbeterde ondersteuning voor reading what is onder de muis pointer as het moves. Het is nu much faster, en het also nu has de ability in some controls zoals standard edit velden, Java en IAccessible2 controls, to read de current word, not just de current object. This may be of some used to vision impared people who just want to read een specific bit of text met de muis.
- Added een nieuw config option, found in de muis settings dialog. Play audio als muis moves, als checked, plays een 40 ms beep each time de muis moves, met its pitch (between 220 en 1760 hz) representing de y axis, en left/right volume, representing de x axis. This enables een blind person to get een rough idea of where de muis is on de scherm as its being moved. This feature also depends on reportObjectUndermuis also being turned on. So this means that if you quickly need to disable both beeps en announcing of objects, then just press NVDA+m. de beeps are also louder or softer depending on how bright de scherm is at that point.


== Object presentatie en interaction ==
- verbeterde ondersteuning voor most common treeview controls. NVDA nu tells you how many items are in de branch als you expand it. Het also announces de level als moving in en out of branches. And, het announces de current item nummer en nummer of items, according to de current branch, not de entire treeview.
- Improved what is announced als focus veranderingen as you move around applicaties or de operating system. nu instead of just hearing de control you land on, you hear informatie about any controls this control is positioned inside of. voor instance if you tab en land on een button inside een groupbox, de groupbox will also get announced.
- NVDA nu tries to speak de message inside many dialog boxes as they appear. This is accurate most of de time, though there are still many dialogs that arn't as good as they could be.
